description:
The 1935 Warner Brothers film “Go Into Your Dance” starred Al Jolson & Ruby Keeler and featured a Harry Warren-Al Dubin song score that included “She’s A Latin From Manhattan,” “The Little Things You Used To Do,” and this popular favorite. See also these three other 1935 versions of “About A Quarter To Nine” posted to the78prof channel:

Ozzie Nelson https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=BvKYjVqOLI8&pp=sAQA
Victor Young https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=eZyYXfJsPLk&pp=sAQA
Johnny Green https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=nCHqRSSAgzk&pp=sAQA

Transferred from 78rpm Bluebird B-5884 - About A Quarter To Nine (Warren-Dubin) by Jack Shilkret & his Orchestra, vocal by Dick Robertson, recorded in NYC March 15, 1935 (actual label scan unavailable)
